From: Moderator-Address
To: Recipient-List
Date: Mon, 22 Mar 1994 13:34:51 +0000
Subject: Internet Digest, volume 42
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: multipart/mixed;
	      boundary="---- main boundary ----"

------ main boundary ----

  ...Introductory text or table of contents...

------ main boundary ----
Content-Type: multipart/digest;
	      boundary="---- next message ----"

------ next message ----

From: someone-else
Date: Fri, 26 Mar 1993 11:13:32 +0200
Subject: my opinion

  ...body goes here ...

------ next message ----

From: someone-else-again
Date: Sat, 27 Mar 1993 12:43:13 +1000
Subject: my opinion about the outer boundary tags
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: multipart/mixed;
	      boundary="---- internal boundary ----"

  ... this is the prologue ...

------ internal boundary ----
Content-Type: text/plain

This is some perfectly boring text, which happens to include the
strings ------ main boundary ---- and ------ main boundary ------,
as well ------ next message ------ and ------ next message ----.

A compliant MIME parser should, at this point, be only looking for
the dashdashdash internal boundary dashdashdashdash

------ internal boundary ----
Content-Type: text/plain

Bing Tiddle Bong. 

------ internal boundary ------

And this is the epilogue

------ next message ------

------ main boundary ------

